A = (4,3);
B = (4,-3);
C = (-4,-3);
D = (-4,3);

draw(A--B--C--D--cycle);

dot("$4 + 3i$", A, NE);
dot("$4 - 3i$", B, SE);
dot("$-4 - 3i$", C, SW);
dot("$-4 + 3i$", D, NW);
[/asy]

The area of this rectangle is $6 \cdot 8 = \boxed{48}.$

By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABC,$
\[\cos \angle ACB = \frac{AC^2 + BC^2 - AB^2}{2 \cdot AC \cdot BC}.\][asy]
